How can we help you?

Frequently Asked Questions

Is the Cadbury e-Gifting Website owned & operated by Cadbury India?

Yes. The Cadbury Joy Deliveries Website (“Website”) is owned and operated by Mondelez India Foods Pvt. Ltd. (“Mondelez”). The order booking, processing and fulfilment is solely done by the authorized sellers registered on the Website (each, a “Registered Seller”). Currently Prestige Pursuits Pvt. Ltd.

How should the chocolates be stored?

The chocolates should be stored not above temperature of 26 degrees Celsius and should be stored in cool, dry conditions away from direct sunlight and strong odours. Please refer to storage condition on the pack of the product.

How can I check the status of my order?

Yes, you can check the status of your order placed on the Registered Seller by logging into your account on the Website. For further information, please refer to your respective Seller FAQs and Seller T&C.

What happens if my item is damaged or I need assistance?

In the unlikely event that your hamper products are damaged in transit, please contact us within 48 hours. Kindly write to us on suggestions@mdlzindia.com with your order number, issue and digital photograph of damaged goods for us to assess and verify its packaging/condition, and we will arrange for a replacement. No Refunds will be processed under any circumstances for products which are damaged in transit.

Phone: 1800-227-080 Mon-Sat 10:00 AM – 6:30 PM (excluding public holidays).

Can I cancel my order/modify the orders?

Once your order has been placed, any cancellation or modification request should be raised to Us within 24 hours of placement of the order for it to be accepted or within such time period and such terms as otherwise stipulated as part of the Seller T&C. Cancellation post shipment: If you wish to cancel an order that has been shipped, please note products once purchased cannot be returned. In case you have additional query’s or issues please get in touch with our Customer Support team on 1800-227-080.

Options for Online Chocolate Delivery

We make it easy for you. Instead of heading to a market and spending time finding what you need in different outlets, we help you send love and chocolates to your loved ones from the comfort of your home, safely and securely and on time.

Fast & Safe Delivery of Chocolates

We deliver overnight (next-day delivery) to Delhi/NCR, Mumbai and Bengaluru locations. For other locations, delivery will take place in seven to eight days. We ensure that the package reaches you undamaged and in good condition. Shipping is free on all orders.

Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)

How many types of chocolates are available?

The entire range of Cadbury chocolates is available here.

When will my order be delivered?

By Express Delivery, it will take us overnight (next day delivery) to deliver to Delhi/NCR, Mumbai and Bengaluru locations. For other locations, delivery will take place in seven to eight days. Shipping is free on all orders.

How do you send the packages?

We send the packages through our regular delivery partners and ensure that the package reaches you undamaged and in good condition.

How long will it take to deliver in India?

By Express Delivery, it will take us overnight (next day delivery) to deliver to Delhi/NCR, Mumbai and Bengaluru locations. For other locations, delivery will take place in seven to eight days. Shipping is free on all orders.

How can I pay?

You can securely make the payment on the website through the payment gateway, it is the standard method used for the purchase of goods online. All major credit/debit cards are accepted; you can also use internet banking to pay.

How to send chocolates online?

There are three basic steps that you need to follow for successfully placing an online delivery order:

  • Explore the products by browsing through each page
  • Choose the one you like and for a dash of personalisation, select an image of the person you’re sending it to and upload it. You can also add a 30-character message
  • All your specifications will be confirmed once you finish the online payment steps

Privacy Preference Center

When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer. More information

Manage Cookie Preferences

Strictly Necessary Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms.    You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.

Performance Cookies

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site.    All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

Functional Cookies

These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages.    If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Targeting Cookies

These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites.    They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising.
